place.name: BARTON TURF
place.gazetteerText: BARTON-TURF, a parish in Tunstead district, Norfolk; 6½ miles SE by S of North Walsham r. station, and 11 NE of Norwich. Post Town, Smallburgh, under Norwich. Acres, 1,599. Real property, £2,643. Pop., 379. Houses, 88. The living is a vicarage, united to the rectory of Irstead, in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £360.* Patron, the Bishop of Norwich. The church is good, and has a lofty tower. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
